First Read: 12-Feb-26
HB432 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 Relating to Montgomery County; to authorize the judge
4 of probate to charge an additional fee for celebrating the
5 rites of matrimony.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
7 Section 1. The Judge of Probate of Montgomery County
8 may charge an additional reasonable fee for providing the
9 service of celebrating the rites of matrimony. The fee
10 authorized by this section shall be in addition to the fee
11 imposed pursuant to Section 12-19-90, Code of Alabama 1975,
12 and shall be retained by the judge of probate or the designee
13 of the judge who solemnized the marriage.
14 Section 2. This act shall become effective immediately.
